Dia. 03 Correct Answer
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par Black's descending move at 1 \cf1\b makes use of the speciality of the corner\cf0\b0 .
\par
\par Both, Black and White have four liberties and White has sente so it still looks like White is going to win the capturing race.
\par
\par However if Black fills the liberties with 3 and 5, White has double shortage of liberties and he can't play from either side, so Black wins the capturing race.
\par
\par Thanks to Black 1, Black's liberties were increased by a lot.
\par }
